opic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.animeinn.com/gallery/amg/thumbs/Amg030.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's really quite funny what watching DBZ can do to ya.</span><hr size=1> AAAARGH!!! to late! I'm a big dragonballZ fan, but i think i can come up with  a good story anyway... i'm in the mood for shôho manga... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=prismrefraction>PrismRefraction</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/18/02 1:21:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=555.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's really quite funny what watching DBZ can do to ya.</span><hr size=1> I write story about normal person in all white room where man goes crazy.  It's my autobiography. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uotakulad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OtakuLad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Canadian <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/18/02 5:23:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=555.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.7hat.com/PKSub/asuka.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's really quite funny what watching DBZ can do to ya.</span><hr size=1> Didn't James Joyce already do that one?...<br><br>heh heh <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=themamba2>TheMamba2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/19/02 12:06:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=555.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's really quite funny what watching DBZ can do to ya.</span><hr size=1> Here's another tip to add onto yours, Kibo. Don't just watch anime. Watch good live action stuff and other good animation types too. For example a very good and WILDLY original anime like Cowboy Bebop is like no other anime I've ever seen. However, it is very similar to some old films I've seen in terms of plot construction and the whole triangle of conflict with Spike, Viscious (spelling?) and Julia. I'm very partial to watching Russian animation because it's just so wierd that its bound to give you some crazy dream you could make into an anime. Also, some computer games these days have some pretty thick plotlines. Max Payne turned me on to a whole new genre of literature with great stories of organised crime and dirty cops. <br><br>I guess what I'm really trying to say is to make a good and orginal anime or manga, don't become completely absorbed in anime and manga because in the end, you're just regurgitating subjects that have been explored again and again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kibo>Kibo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/19/02 4:48:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=555.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's really quite funny what watching DBZ can do to ya.</span><hr size=1> TheMamba2 makes a very GOOD point. If one is trying to create a story, one must not conform to a single genre or syle. Branching out is the best way to build a creative mind. For instance, I'm in a punk band called Trigger Lock. We live in a small town, but this small town has alot of bands (the town of Hillsboro, NH) in the area, most of them suck cuz' they listen to crap like Blink 182 and Sum 41. Our band is known to be pretty good, and why? No, we don't JUST listen to punk rock like the other bands do. We listen to trance, techno, jazz, classical, punk, ska, and other kinds of music. From that we were able to create better songs because we didn't JUST listen to punk rock. The same applies here. Check out all kinds of stories. If you only like anime and manga then don't try and write a story and expect it to get far. Try checking out Marvel, anime, and other. Personally, if you're into the whole cold war deal, then read Rainbow Six for some inspiration. I was totally hooked to Tom Clancy when I read RS. So go ahead, watch movies, read comics, play video games, and if an authority figure tries to stop you then just remind them that because of it you could be making big bucks from your story. Who knows? It COULD happen, couldn't it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uselenesama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>selene sama</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/19/02 7:09:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=555.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's really quite funny what watching DBZ can do to ya.</span><hr size=1>  Hi Hi , <br>  Actually alot of my inspiration comes from songs. For some reasons songs like Natalie Imbruglia's &quot;Torn&quot; or Nina Gordon's &quot; Tonight and the rest of my life&quot;. Totally makes me wanna pick up the nearest G-tip and get drawing. *chuckles* and here lately the old song &quot;Bitch&quot; ( lol my personal theme song by the way) is the basis of my new herione. ^_^ ... or &quot;My way&quot; and I am a huge fan of techno too. It's amazing how much you can be inspired by just a few sweet lines and a good beat. <p>" Can't fight the moon light" Tis I, Selene!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubeldandy2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beldandy2</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_yellowspot." BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/26/02 12:50:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=555.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.noated.com/avatars/beldandy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's really quite funny what watching DBZ can do to ya.</span><hr size=1> i have that thing with songs to! everytime i listnen to Daft Punk, all kinds of story's pop up in my head (though, most of them are about me, using superpowers against my &quot;evil&quot; mathteacher...) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showPrevMessage?topicID=555.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showNextMessage?topicID=555.topic"> Next 